## Development Setup

### Prerequisites

- Java 21 (configured via Gradle toolchain)
- Git
- Access to PEXA Artifactory (for dependencies and publishing)

### Initial Setup

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone git@github.com:PEXA-AU/[your-library-name].git
   cd [your-library-name]
   ```

2. **Verify setup**
   ```bash
   ./gradlew build
   ```

3. **Check current version**
   ```bash
   ./gradlew showVersion
   ```

## Versioning and Release Process

This project uses the **GAP Versioning and Publishing Plugin** for automated semantic versioning. Understanding the versioning process is crucial for contributors.

### Version Management Overview

The library follows [Semantic Versioning 2.0.0](https://semver.org/) with automated version resolution:

- **MAJOR**: Breaking changes to public API
- **MINOR**: New features, backward compatible
- **PATCH**: Bug fixes, backward compatible

### Making Version Changes

```bash
# Increment major version (1.0 → 2.0)
./gradlew incrementMajor

# Increment minor version (1.0 → 1.1)  
./gradlew incrementMinor

# View current version
./gradlew showVersion
```

## Code Quality Standards

### Code Style

- Follow [Kotlin Coding Conventions](https://kotlinlang.org/docs/coding-conventions.html)
- Maximum line length: 120 characters
- Use 4 spaces for indentation
- Document all public APIs with KDoc

### Static Analysis

All code must pass static analysis:

```bash
# Run Detekt analysis
./gradlew detekt

# View report
open build/reports/detekt/detekt.html
```

### Code Coverage

Maintain minimum 80% test coverage:

```bash
# Run tests with coverage
./gradlew test jacocoTestReport

# View coverage report
open build/reports/jacoco/test/html/index.html
```

## Testing Requirements

### Test Categories

1. **Unit Tests** (`src/test/kotlin/`)
   - Fast, isolated tests
   - Mock external dependencies
   - Test individual components

2. **Integration Tests** (`src/testIntegration/kotlin/`)
   - Test component interactions
   - Use Testcontainers for real dependencies
   - Test end-to-end scenarios

### Running Tests

```bash
# Unit tests only
./gradlew test

# Integration tests only
./gradlew testIntegration

# All tests
./gradlew check
```

### Test Requirements

- All new features must include tests
- Bug fixes must include regression tests
- Maintain or improve code coverage
- Tests must be deterministic and fast

